<body>
    <h1>Parameters injection in content views</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>It is possible to dynamically inject variables in content view t=
emplates by listening to the&nbsp;<code><strong>exponential.pre_content_view<=
/strong></code>&nbsp;event.</p>
<p>The event listener method receives an<code>&nbsp;<span>eZ\Publish\Core\M=
VC\Symfony\Event\PreContentViewEvent</span>&nbsp;</code>object</p>
<h3 id=3D"Parametersinjectionincontentviews-Example">Example</h3>
<p>The following example will inject <code>foo</code> and <code>osTypes</co=
de> variables in all content view templates.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">&lt;?php

namespace Acme\DemoBundle\EventListener;
use eZ\Publish\Core\MVC\Symfony\Event\PreContentViewEvent;

class PreContentViewListener
{
    public function onPreContentView( PreContentViewEvent $event )
    {
       &nbsp;// Get content view object and inject whatever no need.
        // You may add some custom business logic here.
        $contentView =3D $event-&gt;getContentView();
        $contentView-&gt;addParameters(
            array(
                 'foo'          =3D&gt; 'bar',
                 'osTypes'      =3D&gt; array( 'osx', 'linux', 'win' )
            )
        );
    }
}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl" style=3D"border-bottom-width: 1px=
;">
<b>Service configuration</b>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">parameters:
    ezdemo.pre_content_view_listener.class: Acme\DemoBundle\EventListener\P=
reContentViewListener

services:
    ezdemo.pre_content_view_listener:
        class: %ezdemo.pre_content_view_listener.class%
        tags:
            - {name: kernel.event_listener, event: exponential.pre_content_vi=
ew, method: onPreContentView}

</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
